"script": "In a crash, an airbag inflates in about 30 milliseconds, faster than you can blink. But it isn't pumped full of air. It's blown open by a controlled explosion. You see, a sensor feels the sudden, violent stop and fires a spark into a pellet of chemical inside the wheel. Then that pellet burns instantly, flooding the bag with harmless nitrogen gas. And this gas slams the nylon outward right as your face arrives. The whole thing inflates and is already deflating before your body has even finished lunging forward.",
